According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Children's Swimwear Market was valued at USD 19.18 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 20.12 billion in 2025 to USD 24.54 billion by 2032, registering a CAGR of 3.8% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing steady growth as parents increasingly prioritize high-quality, UV-protective, and comfortable swimwear for children. Rising participation in swimming lessons, expanding family tourism, growing awareness of water safety, and increasing demand for sustainable apparel are reshaping the children's swimwear industry. Manufacturers are responding with innovative fabrics, eco-friendly materials, and stylish designs that combine safety, durability, and comfort, creating new opportunities across both developed and emerging markets.
